text: Americo-Liberians constitute an ethnic group in Liberia, originating from African American, Afro-Caribbean, and liberated African backgrounds. Their lineage can be traced back to free-born individuals and formerly enslaved African Americans who migrated to Liberia in the 19th century, playing a pivotal role in establishing the nation. This group identifies itself as Americo-Liberians. == References == Category:African-American people Category:Liberia
title: Americo-Liberians
